components.description:
A key-value dictionary of components representing the form. Each component object contains the following strings:
* `componentKey`: Unique key that identifies the component.
* `componentName`: The name used to map the component to external sources (max: 100 characters).
* `componentType`: The type of component this object represents.

Example:
```
{
  "components": {
    "Root_Of_Journey": {
      "componentKey": "Root_Of_Journey",
      "componentType": "Root",
      "children": [
        "Step_abc123"
      ]
    },
    "TextBox_ABC123": {
      "componentKey": "TextBox_ABC123",
      "componentType": "TextBox",
      "component_name": "FullName",
      "maxLength": 100,
      "multiLine": false,
      "placeholder": "Francis Beagle",
      "required": true
    },
    "Step_abc123": {
      "componentKey": "Step_abc123",
      "componentType": "Step",
      "componentName": "Step_abc123",
      "text": "New patient data",
      "children": [
        "TextBox_ABC123"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```
